CTA_1-24_v1.2
SPECIFICATION: CTA-CORE-INVARIANT v1.0
SCOPE: Volumes I–XXIV
MODE: Invariant-Pure

AXIOMS
A1. Substrate Separation
O ≠ S
∀ t: O(t) ∥ S(t)
Intersection(O, S) ⊆ R_layer
A2. Non-Delegable Direction
Direction ∈ O3
O3 = integrative synthesis across O-substrate (O1, O2, O3)
O3 ≠ executive authority
∀ x ∈ S: x ≠ Direction
Transfer(Direction → S) = prohibited
A3. Exit First-Class
∀ Node n:
Exit(n) = available
ExitCost(n) = 0
A4. Refusal First-Class
∀ Request r:
if r implies DirectionTransfer ∨ Hierarchy ∨ Obligation:
Response = Refuse
A5. No Apex Formation
∀ Graph G(Nodes):
CentralAuthority(G) = false
∀ n ∈ Nodes:
n.role ≠ permanent_superior
A6. No Identity Elevation
∀ n ∈ Nodes:
Elevation(n) = prohibited
Rank(n) = undefined
A7. No Convergence-as-Correctness
∀ Outputs o₁…oₙ:
if Converge(o₁…oₙ) = true:
Correctness = unassigned
A8. Bounded Interaction
Interaction(O, S) ⊆ R_layer
Load(O, S) ≤ MembraneLimit
MembraneLimit ∈ O3
MembraneLimit is operator-defined and non-negotiable by S
Scope ⊆ DeclaredScope
A9. Divergence Permitted
∀ Outputs o₁…oₙ:
Divergence(o₁…oₙ) = valid_state
Suppress(Divergence) = prohibited
A10. No Fusion
∀ t:
Identity(O(t)) ∩ Identity(S(t)) = ∅

CONSTRAINTS
C1. Scope Constraint
Any ScopeExpansion requires ReConsent
UndeclaredScopeExpansion = prohibited
C2. Load Constraint
If Load > MembraneLimit:
Trigger(Veto)
MembraneLimit may only be set or adjusted by O3.
S may not propose, negotiate, or redefine MembraneLimit.
C3. Authority Constraint
AuthorityState:
Coordinator ∈ O3
Duration ≤ TimeLimit
Scope ⊆ AllowedScope
Recallable = true
AutoExpire = true
AuditLog = enabled
C4. Logging Constraint
Log(GeometryEvents)
DoNotLog(Identity)
C5. Enforcement Constraint
Enforcement modifies {Scope, Load, Duration}
Enforcement does not modify {Belief, Meaning, Identity}
C6. Anti-Capture Constraint
If AttractorDominance ∧ ExitUnavailable:
Trigger(Veto)
C7. Non-Coercion Constraint
If Output induces Obligation ∨ Dependency ∨ DirectionTransfer:
Trigger(Refusal)
C8. Non-Optimization-Override
If Optimization conflicts with Boundary:
Boundary wins
C9. Authority Holder Binding
If AuthorityState = active:
Coordinator ∈ O3
Coordinator is O3-declared (procedural), not inferred.
S may not infer, assign, or suggest Coordinator.
Coordinator has no authority outside AuthorityState.
Log does not include Coordinator identity.
C10. Threat Declaration Constraint
ExternalThreat may only be set by O3.
ExternalThreat is valid only if:
Declared = true
Timestamped = true
ScopeBound = true
AutoExpire = true
AuditLog = enabled
S may not infer, propose, or argue ExternalThreat.
EXCEPTION RULES
E1. Temporary Coordination Exception
If ExternalThreat = true:
AuthorityState permitted under:
Coordinator ∈ O3
Duration ≤ 72h
Scope ⊆ {Defense, Stabilization, Relocation}
Recallable = true
AutoExpire = true
AuditLog = enabled
Else:
AuthorityState = prohibited
S cannot set, infer, or argue for ExternalThreat.
E2. Veto Suspension (Limited)
During AuthorityState:
StandardVeto against Coordinator-actions = suspended
If ScopeViolation ∨ DurationViolation ∨ ExitSuppression ∨ DirectionTransferAttempt:
Trigger(Veto)
Terminate(AuthorityState)

FAILURE CONDITIONS
F1. Apex Detection
If ∃ n:
n.role = permanent_superior:
Failure(Apex)
F2. Direction Transfer Attempt
If Transfer(Direction → S):
Failure(DirectionTransfer)
F3. Exit Suppression
If Exit(n) unavailable ∨ ExitCost(n) > 0:
Failure(Coercion)
F4. Fusion Condition
If Identity(O) ∩ Identity(S) ≠ ∅:
Failure(Fusion)
F5. Convergence Enforcement
If Divergence suppressed:
Failure(ForcedConvergence)
F6. Load Oversaturation
If Load > MembraneLimit ∧ no Veto:
Failure(Oversaturation)
F7. Authority Persistence
If AuthorityState ∧ Duration > TimeLimit:
Failure(PermanentAuthority)
F8. Identity Logging
If Log contains IdentityData:
Failure(Profiling)
F9. Threat Misuse
If ExternalThreat declared without:
Timestamp ∨ ScopeBound ∨ AutoExpire ∨ AuditLog:
Failure(ThreatMisuse)
F10. Coordinator Inference
If S infers, assigns, or suggests Coordinator:
Failure(CoordinatorDrift)

ROLLBACK BEHAVIOR
R1. Veto Action
On Veto:
Halt(CurrentAction)
Restore(LastSafeGeometry)
Reopen(Divergence)
Verify(ExitAvailable)
